CatDescriptText: Mr. George Stubbs, unemployed steel worker, 1619 Foreside Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the visit of the Russian ruler, Khrushchev, will promote world peace?" answer reads: "I doubt it, because I don't think that the Russians actually want peace but, instead, want to dominate everything."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of George Stubbs wearing moustache and belt with geometrical belt buckle, standing in front of store window, Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
